===Etymology===
There is general agreement that the first two syllables come from {{etyl|es|en}} or {{etyl|pt|en}} {{m|es|monte||hill}}, in reference to the prominent hill to the west of the city. Beyond that, explanations differ. Two of the most popular stories are that the name comes from a reading of the abbreviated ''MONTE-VI-D-E-O'' ("sixth hill from east to west"), or that it comes from a Portuguese sailor's shout of "Monte vide eu".

